Title: Mariathasan2018_PDL1_treatment
Description: Processed RNA-seq data, quantified as counts and TPM, for bladder cancer samples pre anti-PDL1 immunotherapy. Information on patient's tumor mutational burden and response to anti-PD1 treatment is also provided. Represented as a SummarizedExperiment; derived from IMvigor210CoreBiologies R package (Mariathasan et al., Nature, 2018) under the CC-BY license.
DataProvider: Mariathasan S, Turley S, Nickles D et al., â€œTGF-b attenuates tumor response to PD-L1 blockade by contributing to exclusion of T cells.

Title: RMTLR_TCGA_cancer_spec_trained_models
Description: Cancer-specifc model parameters learned during training for different quantitative descriptors using Regularized Multi-Task Linear Regression (RMTLR) algorithm with randomized cross-validation repeated 100 times. A total of 100 models are available for each task, here 10 tasks were used. Also, information on training set statistics (i.e. meand and standard deviation) are also provided for normalizing the test set accordingly. Represented as a list object with both cancer-specific models and statistics about the training dataset.

Title: TCGA_pancancer_per_gene_statistics
Description: Mean and standard deviation of the expression of each gene across all TCGA cancer types. Represented as a list object with both statistical measures. Helpful for normalization steps.

Title: proxies_genes
Description: Genes used to compute correlated proxies of immune response.

Title: Intercellular_network
Description: Cancer-specific intercellular networks based on literature supported pairs in the Ramilowski database (Ramilowski et al., Nat.Commun., 2015), filtering for 24 cell types acknowledged to be present in the TME. Additionally, a pan-cancer cell type is included using data from the CCLE (Barretina et al., Nature, 2012) by computing the median expression of each gene across cell lines related to the selected cancer types. Represented as a list object with cancer-specific intercellular networks information.

Title: LR_TCGA_frequency
Description: Frequency of each ligand-receptor pair across the whole TCGA database.

Title: Grouping_LR_pairs
Description: Information on how ligand-receptor pairs were grouped because of sharing the same gene either as ligand or receptor. Represented as a list object with information to group certain LR pairs.

Title: HGNC_checker
Description: Information on gene symbols approved annotations. Represented as a matrix, derived from https://www.genenames.org/tools/multi-symbol-checker/.

Title: RIR_signature
Description: Gene signatures included in the immune resistance program from Jerby-Arnon et al., 2018 Represented as a list object obtained from https://github.com/livnatje/ImmuneResistance/blob/master/Results/Signatures/resistance.program.RData.
